  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The simulation pipeline is built on a multi-physics FEA/CFD solver stack comprising OpenFOAM-derived turbulence modules, a Python-based hemolysis damage accumulation post-processor, and a parallelized MPI job scheduler. All simulation runs completed nominally across the five flow-speed operating points evaluated.",
