    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-mesh-independence-001",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence study — nominal completion",
      "description": "Three mesh refinement levels (coarse 2.1M cells, medium 5.4M cells, fine 11.8M cells) were evaluated. The solver executed to completion at all refinement levels with no interruptions. Richardson extrapolation yielded a grid convergence index below 2% for the relative hemolysis index QoI. All runs reported nominal completion status."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-experimental-comparison-001",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental hemolysis comparison — nominal completion",
      "description": "Simulated normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against in vitro measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump test dataset across 5 flow-speed operating points. Predicted NIH values fell within ±15% of experimental means at all operating points. All CFD runs completed nominally with solver residuals converging to 1e-6 within the prescribed iteration budget."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-turbulence-model-sensitivity-001",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence model sensitivity — nominal completion",
      "description": "SST k-omega and realizable k-epsilon turbulence models were both exercised across the five operating points. The Python hemolysis damage accumulation post-processor ingested both sets of velocity gradient fields and produced RH index outputs for each. All simulation runs and post-processing executions completed nominally with no anomalies reported in the job scheduler logs."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-predicate-comparison-001",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Predicate device relative hemolysis comparison — nominal completion",
      "description": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) was computed for all 5 flow-speed combinations against the predicate device reference. RH remained below 1.0 across all conditions, satisfying the acceptance criterion. The MPI-parallelized solver completed all 10 ensemble runs (2 turbulence models × 5 operating points) with nominal exit codes and no job failures recorded by the scheduler."
    }
  ],
