      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the standard hemolysis metrics specified in ASTM F1841 and referenced in FDA guidance for CPB device submissions. Both QoIs are directly traceable to the clinical hemolysis risk metric. Their use in this assessment is fully justified."
